// Chinese deities × 12 — the Daoist / Buddhist / folk pantheon — SEO funnel.
// /gab44/chinese-gods (index) + /gab44/chinese-gods/{slug}.
//
// Tenth great pantheon on gab44 after Olympians, Norse, Hindu, Egyptian, Celtic,
// Orishas, Mesopotamian, Aztec, and Shinto. The MOST-POPULOUS pantheon by living
// adherents (~300-400M Chinese folk-religion practitioners + the Mazu, Guanyin,
// and Guan Yu transnational diaspora cults across Taiwan, Hong Kong, Singapore,
// Malaysia, the Chinatowns of the Americas and Europe). The only pantheon that
// survived a state-sponsored Cultural-Revolution destruction (1966-1976, ~70-90%
// of Buddhist and Daoist temples destroyed) and a contemporary "Sinicization of
// religion" (中国化, zhōngguóhuà) campaign under Xi Jinping (2015-). The pantheon
// that integrates Daoism, Buddhism, Confucian ancestor-veneration, and folk
// religion into the unique San Jiao (三教, "Three Teachings") syncretism. The
// only pantheon whose celestial bureaucracy mirrors imperial administration —
// the Jade Emperor's heavenly court has ministries, vice-ministers, demotions,
// promotions, and bureaucratic memos written on paper joss-money. Closes the
// East-Asian-continental gap on gab44 (Shinto closed the Japanese-archipelago
// gap; Chinese closes the mainland) and creates the structural peer-cluster to
// the existing Chinese-zodiac module (chinese.ts) which until this ship was
// the only Chinese-cultural surface on gab44 with no deity-pantheon behind it.
//
// Three families × 4 gods:
//  - Celestial Sovereigns (天界): the cosmic-bureaucratic register — Yu-Huang /
//    Jade Emperor the supreme sovereign of heaven; Xi-Wang-Mu the Queen Mother
//    of the West with her peach-of-immortality grove; Pangu the cosmic giant
//    who separated heaven and earth from primordial chaos; Nüwa the serpent-
//    bodied creator of humanity and patcher of the broken sky.
//  - Compassion, Earth & Scholar (慈悲・大地・文): the moral-emotional-civilian
//    register — Guanyin the bodhisattva of compassion (the Chinese gender-flip
//    of Avalokiteśvara, the single most-worshipped female deity on Earth);
//    Wenchang Wang the patron of literature and the imperial-examination scholar;
//    Tu Di Gong the local-earth-god of every neighborhood altar in the Chinese
//    world; Caishen the god of wealth whose New-Year-welcoming ritual is the
//    most-performed annual religious act in the Chinese-speaking world.
//  - Warriors, Trickster & Underworld (武・妖・冥): the heroic/disruptive/judicial
//    register — Guan Yu the historical Three Kingdoms general deified as god of
//    loyalty/war/business (worshipped by Hong Kong police AND Hong Kong triads);
//    Sun Wukong the Monkey King of Journey to the West, arguably the most-
//    adapted character in world literature; Yan Wang the king of the Ten Courts
//    of Hell; Mazu the goddess of the sea, UNESCO-listed transnational cult.
//
// Source-honest from the *Daodejing* (道德经, c. 4th c. BCE attributed to
// Laozi — the foundational Daoist text); the *Zhuangzi* (庄子, c. 4th-3rd c.
// BCE — the second foundational Daoist text); the *Shanhaijing* (山海经,
// Classic of Mountains and Seas, c. 4th c. BCE-1st c. CE — the oldest extant
// catalogue of Chinese deities, monsters, geography); the *Liexian Zhuan*
// (列仙传, c. 1st c. BCE-1st c. CE, attributed to Liu Xiang — Biographies of
// Immortals); the *Baopuzi* (抱朴子, c. 320 CE Ge Hong — the foundational
// alchemical-Daoist text); the *Yunji Qiqian* (云笈七签, c. 1019 CE Zhang
// Junfang — the encyclopedic Daoist canon-digest); the *Taishang Ganying
// Pian* (太上感应篇, c. 12th c. — the Treatise on Action and Response, the
// foundational popular-morality Daoist text); the *Lotus Sutra* (妙法莲华经
// Miaofa Lianhua Jing) Chapter 25 the *Universal Gate of Avalokiteśvara*
// (普门品 Pumen Pin), the textual basis of the Guanyin cult; the *Heart Sutra*
// (心经 Xin Jing); the *Pure Land Sutras*; the *Romance of the Three Kingdoms*
// (三国演义 Sanguo Yanyi, c. 14th c. Luo Guanzhong — the historical-literary
// source for the Guan Yu cult); *Journey to the West* (西游记 Xiyou Ji, c.
// 1592 Wu Cheng'en — the Sun Wukong source, the most-adapted Chinese novel);
// the *Investiture of the Gods* (封神演义 Fengshen Yanyi, c. 1567 Xu Zhonglin
// — the systematic late-Ming theogonic novel that codified the Daoist pantheon
// for popular consumption); the *Yuli Baochao* (玉历宝钞, c. 12th c. — the Jade
// Records illustrating the Ten Courts of Hell); the *Mazu Lin'gan Lu* (妈祖灵
// 感录 — the annals of Mazu apparitions); the *Huainanzi* (淮南子, c. 139 BCE
// — including the Nüwa-patches-the-sky narrative); the *Sou Shen Ji* (搜神记
// c. 350 CE Gan Bao — In Search of the Supernatural); the *Liji* (礼记 Book
// of Rites) for Tu Di Gong and ancestral rites; the Three Pure Ones (三清
// Sānqīng) iconography of Daoist temple cosmology; modern scholarship: Joseph
// Needham *Science and Civilisation in China* 1954- 27 vols; Anne Birrell
// *Chinese Mythology: An Introduction* (Johns Hopkins 1993); C.A.S. Williams
// *Outlines of Chinese Symbolism and Art Motives* 1932/1976; Henri Maspero
// *Le Taoïsme et les religions chinoises* 1971 (Eng. tr. 1981); Kristofer
// Schipper *The Taoist Body* 1982/1993; Chün-fang Yü *Kuan-yin: The Chinese
// Transformation of Avalokiteśvara* (Columbia 2001 — the canonical Guanyin
// scholarship); Stephen F. Teiser *The Scripture on the Ten Kings* (Hawaii
// 1994) and *The Ghost Festival in Medieval China* 1988; Robert Hymes *Way
// and Byway: Taoism, Local Religion, and Models of Divinity in Sung and
// Modern China* (Berkeley 2002); Patricia Buckley Ebrey *Cambridge Illustrated
// History of China* 1996; John Lagerwey & Pierre Marsone eds. *Modern Chinese
// Religion* (Brill 2014- 4 vols); Barend ter Haar *Guan Yu: The Religious
// Afterlife of a Failed Hero* (Oxford 2017 — the canonical Guan Yu scholarship);
// James Watson "Standardizing the Gods: The Promotion of Tian Hou (Mazu) along
// the South China Coast" (1985); Sarah Allan *The Shape of the Turtle* 1991
// for Pangu/Nüwa cosmogonies; Edward L. Davis *Society and the Supernatural in
// Song China* 2001; Vincent Goossaert *The Taoists of Peking* 2007 and *The
// Religious Question in Modern China* (with David Palmer, 2011); Adam Yuet
// Chau *Miraculous Response: Doing Popular Religion in Contemporary China* 2006.
//
// Shadow-honest about: the Cultural Revolution (1966-1976) systematic destruction
// of ~70-90% of all Buddhist + Daoist + folk temples in mainland China, including
// the smashing of statues, burning of scriptures, defrocking of clergy, conversion
// of temples to warehouses-schools-factories, and Red Guard violence against
// religious practitioners; the contemporary "Sinicization of religion" campaign
// (中国化, zhōngguóhuà) under Xi Jinping (2015-) requiring all religions to
// "conform to Chinese socialist core values" and the demolition of crosses /
// removal of children from religious education / surveillance of clergy; the
// Falun Gong suppression (1999-) and the broader CCP framing of folk religion
// as "feudal superstition" (封建迷信 fēngjiàn míxìn); the 19th-c. Western
// Orientalist construction of "Chinese religion" as primitive ancestor-worship
// (Edkins, Legge, Lévy-Bruhl, the Fu Manchu and Yellow Peril tropes); the
// missionary erasure of folk religion as the demonic background against which
// Christianity was to be preached (the 1715-1742 Rites Controversy that
// Vatican-suppressed the Jesuit accommodation of Confucian rites); the white-
// New-Age "Tao of Pooh" / "Tao of physics" commodification stripping Daoism
// of its Chinese-language, ritual, and clergy infrastructure; the gym-Tai-Chi /
// gym-yoga register that detaches body-practice from cultivation-tradition;
// the Mazu Taiwan-vs-mainland political instrumentalization (the PRC's
// promotion of cross-strait Mazu pilgrimages as soft-power unification tool);
// the Guan Yu / triad-mafia / Hong-Kong-police double-worship as the most-
// visible internal contradiction of any deity-cult in the modern world; the
// Disney-Mulan / Disney-and-Marvel-Shang-Chi / Dragon-Ball / Naruto / Avatar:
// The Last Airbender / Kung Fu Panda Western flattening of the Sun-Wukong-and-
// Eight-Immortals register into generic "Asian-mystical" content; the Hollywood
// "yellow-face" tradition (Charlie Chan, Fu Manchu, Mickey Rooney's Mr Yunioshi);
// the academic Sinology tradition's privileging of Confucian-elite-textual
// materials over Daoist-popular-ritual materials (corrected only since the
// 1980s by the Schipper / Strickmann / Bokenkamp / Verellen "field Taoism"
// scholarship); the white-occult appropriation of the I Ching (already on
// gab44) without the Daoist-cosmological infrastructure that produced it; the
// modern Falun Gong appropriation of Daoist cosmology for new-religious-
// movement purposes that mainstream Daoist clergy largely reject; the
// contemporary Confucius-Institute soft-power deployment of "Chinese culture"
// as a CCP-curated export-product; the destruction of c. 16,000 mosques in
// Xinjiang 2017- and the parallel demolition of c. 1,000 Tibetan-Buddhist
// monasteries — named per deity where the connection is direct.

